# DATA STRUCTURES IMPLEMENTATION REPORT

## 1. Aim

To implement:
- Binary Search Tree (BST)
- Graph Traversals (BFS and DFS)
- Hash Table using Separate Chaining

---

## 2. Binary Search Tree

Operations implemented:
- Insert
- Search
- Inorder Traversal

BST stores elements in sorted order.

---

## 3. Graph Implementation

A directed weighted graph was implemented using adjacency list representation.

Traversals performed:
- BFS (Breadth First Search)
- DFS (Depth First Search)

Traversal orders were printed.

---

## 4. Hash Table

Hash table was implemented using separate chaining to handle collisions.

Operations implemented:
- Insert
- Search
- Delete

Collision handling was demonstrated successfully.

---

## 5. Conclusion

All required data structures were implemented successfully.
The program demonstrated BST operations, graph traversals, and hash table collision handling correctly.